All R packages which are supported by htmlwidgets can be exported from R into Tiddlywiki with an unique interface through js widget `htmlwidgets` and then display as interactive figures. We could utilise all benefits of R to quickly data processing and visualisation to generate interactive figures. 

!! From R to Tiddlywiki

For R users, R scripts can be developed as normal ways to produce an interactive figure, then transfer into Tiddlywiki. R function [ext[tw_widget|https://rtiddlywiki.bangyou.me/reference/tw_widget.html]] can be used to produce Wikitext which will call [[htmlwidgets|doc/htmlwidgets-widget]] with specified data argument. 

* For node.js users, Wikitext can be directly `PUT` into Tiddlywiki through R function [ext[put_tiddler|https://rtiddlywiki.bangyou.me/reference/put_tiddler.html]].
* For single file users, Wikitext can be saved into text file and manually copy into Tiddlywiki.

See [[example R scripts|doc/From-R-to-Tiddlywiki]].

!! Filter operator

If your data already store in Tiddlywiki, or you want to dynamically generate interactive figures, several filter operators are developed to generate required json data for [[htmlwidgets|doc/htmlwidgets-widget]]. 



